    "intro": "Interpretation moves from the text's observable surface to its intended meaning — what the author is arguing, what theological realities the narrative encodes, and how the chapter fits the canonical arc from Deuteronomy's commands to Israel's covenant failures across the historical books. The movements below trace the chapter's argument through five pericopes, giving particular attention to the legal, theological, and redemptive-historical dimensions that a surface reading can miss.",
